==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dreadnaught
<hw>Dread"naught`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
fearless person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: A garment made of very thick cloth, that can
defend against storm and cold; also, the cloth itself;
fearnaught.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A <er>dreadnought</er>, in either sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dreadnought</ent>⟦br⟧
